Issue Catalogue

🟡 BOOK-01 — Boolean Flags Stored as bit — Cannot Aggregate Directly
Table: bookings · Columns: is_canceled, is_repeated_guest, is_room_type_changed · Type: bit


Description:

Three business-critical flag columns are stored as SQL bit (boolean). Most BI tools including instaBI cannot SUM() a boolean field directly, making rate calculations impossible without a workaround.


Column	Business Use	Problem
is_canceled	Cancellation rate = SUM / COUNT	Cannot SUM bit in most BI tools
is_repeated_guest	Repeated guest rate	Cannot SUM bit in most BI tools
is_room_type_changed	Room change rate	Cannot SUM bit in most BI tools

Impact: Dashboard KPIs for cancellation rate, repeated guest rate, and room type change rate cannot be built through drag-and-drop in instaBI without numeric equivalents.


Fix applied in `fct_bookings`:

CAST(is_canceled AS FLOAT)          AS is_canceled_float,
1.0 - CAST(is_canceled AS FLOAT)    AS confirmed_float,
CAST(is_repeated_guest AS INT)      AS is_repeated_guest_int,
CAST(is_room_type_changed AS INT)   AS is_room_type_changed_int

Usage in instaBI:

Cancellation Rate   = SUM(is_canceled_float)        / COUNT(booking_key)
Repeated Guest Rate = SUM(is_repeated_guest_int)    / COUNT(booking_key)
Room Change Rate    = SUM(is_room_type_changed_int) / COUNT(booking_key)


🟡 BOOK-02 — historical_cancellation_rate NULL for 92.2% of Rows
Table: bookings → fct_bookings · Column: historical_cancellation_rate · Type: decimal(5,4)


Description:

A guest-level risk score derived from prior booking history. NULL means the guest is first-time — both previous_cancellations and previous_bookings_not_canceled are 0.


Value	Rows	%
NULL (first-time guests)	108,384	92.2%
0.0 (never canceled before)	2,768	2.4%
1.0 (always canceled before)	5,832	5.0%
Between 0 and 1	592	0.5%

Formula: previous_cancellations / NULLIF(previous_cancellations + previous_bookings_not_canceled, 0)


Impact: AVG(historical_cancellation_rate) across all rows is misleading — NULL rows are silently excluded. Average among non-NULL rows ≈ 0.65. Always filter WHERE historical_cancellation_rate IS NOT NULL before aggregating.


No fix needed — NULL is semantically correct. Enforce as a usage convention.



🟡 BOOK-03 — adr = 0 for 178 Rows (Complimentary Stays)
Table: bookings → fct_bookings · Column: adr · Type: decimal(10,2)


Description:

178 bookings (0.15%) have adr = 0 — complimentary or internal stays with no charged rate. Valid bookings but silently lower AVG(adr) and produce estimated_revenue = 0.


Impact: Minor. Recommended filter for ADR and revenue analysis: WHERE adr > 0.



🟡 BOOK-04 — 23 Zero-Night Stays (total_nights = 0)
Table: bookings → fct_bookings · Column: total_nights · Type: tinyint


Description:

23 bookings (0.02%) have total_nights = 0 — likely same-day check-outs or day-use bookings where stays_in_week_nights + stays_in_weekend_nights = 0.


Impact: estimated_revenue = 0 even when adr > 0. Slightly understates AVG(total_nights). Recommended filter for stay-length analysis: WHERE total_nights > 0.



🟡 FCT-01 — reservation_status Not Carried to Mart
Table: fct_bookings · Column: missing


Description:

bookings contains reservation_status (values: Check-Out / Canceled / No-Show) which passes through stg_bookings and int_bookings_flagged but was not included in `fct_bookings`. Only is_canceled (boolean) is available, which cannot distinguish No-Show from a standard cancellation.


Status	Available in fct?
Check-Out	❌ Inferred only from is_canceled = false
Canceled	✅ is_canceled = true
No-Show	❌ Not distinguishable

Impact: Dashboard cannot report No-Show rate separately from Cancellation rate.


Recommended fix: Add reservation_status to fct_bookings in CODE mode.



🟡 FCT-02 — adr_adjusted and estimated_revenue = 0 for All Canceled Bookings
Table: fct_bookings · Columns: adr_adjusted, estimated_revenue


Description:

By design, both columns are set to 0 when is_canceled = true, affecting 44,188 rows (37.58%).


Column	Zero rows	%	Reason
adr_adjusted	44,188	37.58%	Set to 0 when is_canceled = true
estimated_revenue	44,188	37.58%	Set to 0 when is_canceled = true

This is intentional. However it causes AVG(adr_adjusted) to appear much lower than AVG(adr) (City Hotel: $62.49 vs $106.74). Always filter WHERE is_canceled = false for revenue and adjusted ADR analysis.



