🟡 DIM-02 — dim_arrival_date Covers Dates Before Booking Data Range
Table: dim_arrival_date


Description:

The date dimension starts October 2014 but the earliest booking arrives July 2015. Months between October 2014 and June 2015 exist in the dimension but have no matching bookings — producing 0 revenue and 0 bookings in any chart that LEFT JOINs from the date dimension.


Period	In dim_arrival_date	Bookings
Oct 2014 – Jun 2015	✅ Present	0
Jul 2015 – Aug 2017	✅ Present	117,576

Recommended action: Apply a date range filter in dashboard charts, e.g. WHERE year >= 2016 OR (year = 2015 AND month_number >= 7).



🟡 DIM-03 — dim_country Contains Sentinel Continent Values
Table: dim_country · Column: continent


Description:

Two continent values are semantically invalid and will pollute continent-level charts.


Continent	Issue
'Antarctica'	Likely unmapped country code or data entry error
'Unknown'	Country could not be mapped to a continent

Recommended action: Identify the country_code values behind these rows. Remap 'Antarctica' to the correct continent. Replace 'Unknown' with NULL or a defined fallback.



🟡 DIM-04 — dim_assigned_room Has 2 More Room Types Than dim_reserved_room
Tables: dim_assigned_room (12 rows) vs dim_reserved_room (10 rows)


Description:

2 room type codes exist in dim_assigned_room that are not in dim_reserved_room. Guests cannot reserve these types directly — they are likely upgrade or overflow rooms assigned at check-in.


Impact: Room-type comparison charts (reserved vs assigned) will have unmatched codes on the assigned side.


Recommended action: Document which 2 codes are assigned-only and add an is_reservable flag to dim_assigned_room.



